main event: Two couples observed a white light in the sky that changed to orange with flashing red lights near Sullivan, Wisconsin on June 23, 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed for 45 minutes., The light changed color from white to orange and had flashing red lights., The object did not emit any sound or exhaust., It was reported that the object hovered and then dropped out of sight., Observers had clear weather conditions during the sighting.
sighted object: one white light turning to orange with flashing red lights
witness description: Two couples, one being a salesman and the other a sod firm manager, plus a deputy sheriff.
